<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-1164] Improve how ConcurrentMergeScheduler handles too-many-merges case</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-1164</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;CMS now lets you set &quot;maxMergeThreads&quot; to control max # simultaneous&lt;br/&gt;
merges.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;However, when CMS hits that max, it still allows further merges to&lt;br/&gt;
run, by running them in the foreground thread.  So if you set this max&lt;br/&gt;
to 1, and use 1 thread to add docs, you can get 2 merges running at&lt;br/&gt;
once (which I think is broken).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I think, instead, CMS should pause the foreground thread, waiting&lt;br/&gt;
until the number of merge threads drops below the limit.  Then, kick&lt;br/&gt;
off the backlog merge in a thread and return control back to primary&lt;br/&gt;
thread.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
